Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/recordOf
Object: Relates a document to the calendared event it records.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/partOfSeries
Object: Relates a business item to a business item series it is part of.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/cancelledAt
Object: The time at which a calendared event was cancelled.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/CalendaredEvent
Object: An event during which business items happen.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/notReached
Object: A boolean which is true when a calendared event was not reached or became unavailable for disposal.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/hasBusinessItemType
Object: Relates a business item to its type.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/BusinessItem
Object: An item of business conducted either within or outside Parliament. For example: a second reading debate, the tabling of an early day motion, a laying of a paper or the making of a statutory instrument by a government minister.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/takesPlaceIn
Object: Relates a calendared event to the place it occurs.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/BusinessItemType
Object: The type of a business item. For example: a committee visit, a committee evidence session or a chamber debate.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/Document
Object: A document being a FRBR work.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/Place
Object: A place named in a geography.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/calendarisation
Object: Describes the process of setting a time or date at which a business item is expected to take place.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/
Object: A model describing items of business taking place in Parliament or outside Parliament - as part of a process involving Parliament - and their scheduling.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/disposedOfAt
Object: The time at which an agenda item was completed.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/BusinessItemSeries
Object: A series of regularly recurring business items. For example: questions to the Department of Health and Social Care.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/containsBusinessItem
Object: Allows a business item to be nested inside another business item. For example, a committee meeting during a committee visit.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/business-item/followedBy
Object: Relates a calendared event to a subsequent calendared event
